Peste des petits ruminants, Bhutan
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 6 Apr 2018 from Dr. Tashi Samdup, Director General, Department of Livestock, Ministry of Agriculture and Forests, Thimphu, Bhutan

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 28 Mar 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 30 Mar 2018
Report date: 6 Apr 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 6 Apr 2018
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 23 Nov 2015
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Peste des petits ruminants virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (BHT_PPR_2018_001): Kharbandi, Phuentsholing, Chhukha
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Mar 2018
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Other
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Goats / 3 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The goat was bought and brought illegally from across the border (Indo-Bhutan border) for religious purposes and was left to graze openly at Kharbandi area of Phuentsholing sub-district.
Outbreak statistics:
Species/ Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Goats/ 33.33 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Introduction of new live animals, Illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments:

Control measures Supportive therapy using analgesics, antipyretics, antihistamines, and antibiotics.
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, disinfection, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: screening, quarantine

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Centre for Animal Health (national laboratory) / Goat / rapid test / 30 Mar 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

